.html#Subtype\">//</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/NumberField/CanonicalEmbedding/Basic.html#NumberField.mixedEmbedding.norm\">mixedEmbedding.norm</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">a</span></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">}</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For `s : ℝ`, the number of principal nonzero ideals in `𝓞 K` divisible par `J` of norm `≤ s`\nmultiplied by the order of the torsion of `K` is equal to the number of elements in `idealSet K J`\nof norm `≤ s`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/NumberField/CanonicalEmbedding/FundamentalCone.html#NumberField.mixedEmbedding.fundamentalCone.card_isPrincipal_dvd_norm_le","kind":"theorem","line":576,"name":"NumberField.mixedEmbedding.fundamentalCone.card_isPrincipal_dvd_norm_le","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/NumberField/CanonicalEmbedding/FundamentalCone.lean#L576-L608"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/NumberField/CanonicalEmbedding/FundamentalCone.html#NumberField.mixedEmbedding.fundamentalCone.idealSetEquivNorm\"><span class=\"name\">NumberField</span>.<span class=\"name\">mixedEmbedding</span>.<span class=\"name\">fundamentalCone</span>.<span class=\"name\">idealSetEquivNorm</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">K</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/NumberTheor